Hotel guests and residents at an historic San Francisco Bay Area hotel and social club were evacuated on Tuesday afternoon after a resident committed suicide in her room using a toxic chemical.

The 80-year-old woman, whose named hasn’t been released, killed herself in her apartment on the third floor of the landmark Berkeley City Club.

Police spokesman Officer Ethell Wilson said hazardous materials crews and bomb squad technicians responded to the call on the third floor of the six-story landmark shortly before 2 p.m. 

